---
import Base from '../../hubs/web0/layouts/Base.astro';
import ToolLayout from '../../hubs/web0/components/ToolLayout.astro';
---
<Base
  title="HTTP Security Headers Audit - CSP, HSTS grade | web0.dev"
  description="Grade a site's HTTP response security headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, and more). Paste headers from DevTools or curl. Audited 100% locally, nothing uploaded.">
  <ToolLayout name="HTTP Security Headers Audit">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <div class="inline-flex border border-rule rounded overflow-hidden mb-4">
        <button id="mode-paste" class="label px-3 py-1.5" aria-selected="true">paste</button>
        <button id="mode-fetch" class="label px-3 py-1.5 border-l border-rule" aria-selected="false">fetch url</button>
      </div>

      <div id="paste-panel" class="space-y-3">
        <textarea id="headers-paste" rows="8" spellcheck="false"
          placeholder="Paste raw response headers, e.g. the output of `curl -I https://example.com`, or DevTools → Network → (request) → Response Headers"
          class="w-full bg-raised border border-rule rounded px-3 py-2 font-mono text-sm text-ink resize-y focus:outline-none focus:border-accent"></textarea>
        <button id="headers-audit-btn" class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-medium bg-accent text-accent-ink px-4 py-2 rounded">Audit headers</button>
      </div>

      <div id="fetch-panel" class="hidden space-y-3">
        <div class="flex gap-2">
          <input id="headers-url" type="text" placeholder="https://example.com" spellcheck="false"
            class="flex-1 bg-raised border border-rule rounded px-3 py-2 font-mono text-sm text-ink focus:outline-none focus:border-accent" />
          <button id="headers-fetch-btn" class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-medium bg-accent text-accent-ink px-4 py-2 rounded">Fetch</button>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted">Best-effort. Browsers only expose cross-origin headers the server allows via CORS. Paste mode gives a complete audit.</p>
      </div>

      <p id="headers-status" class="label mt-4 min-h-[1.2em]"></p>
      <div id="headers-grade" class="hidden border border-rule rounded p-4 mt-2"></div>
      <div id="headers-findings" class="mt-4"></div>
    </div>
    <div slot="explainer">
      <p>This grades the security-relevant HTTP response headers a site sends. The audit runs
      entirely in your browser. In <strong>paste mode</strong> nothing is sent anywhere.</p>
      <p class="mt-3"><strong>How to copy a site's headers:</strong></p>
      <ol class="mt-1 list-decimal list-inside space-y-0.5">
        <li>Open DevTools (F12) → <strong>Network</strong> tab, reload the page.</li>
        <li>Click the top (document) request → <strong>Headers</strong> → <strong>Response Headers</strong>.</li>
        <li>Copy them and paste above. Or run <code>curl -I https://example.com</code> and paste that.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </ToolLayout>
</Base>
<script>
  import { headersSection } from '../../hubs/web0/scripts/tools/headers';
  headersSection();
</script>
